==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
From old [[Irish]] ''inghean''.

===Noun===
'''nighean''' {{f}}

#A [[daughter]], female [[offspring]].
#In common usage, a [[maiden]] or [[girl]].
#:''"An cluinn thu mi, mo nighean donn?      ("Will you listen to me, my brown-haired girl?")''

